### Component 6 тАФ Semantic Event Layer (Architecture Design)

This is a **future pipeline**, but we design the interface now so the DB schema can accommodate it.

```
Stage 1.6 (Now):   Store raw events + screen snapshots
Stage 2.0 (Next):  Rule-based normalizer runs post-hoc
Stage 3.0 (Future): LLM normalizer via Pinecone/OpenAI
```

**Rule-based normalizer examples:**
```kotlin
fun normalize(events: List<RichEventRecord>): SemanticEvent? {
    // Detect "BOOK_BUS" intent
    if (events.any { it.screenName?.contains("SeatLayout") == true } &&
        events.any { it.buttonLabel == "Continue" }) {
        return SemanticEvent(
            action = "BOOK_BUS",
            params = mapOf(
                "source" to editableFields.find { it.hint == "From" }?.value,
                "destination" to editableFields.find { it.hint == "To" }?.value
            )
        )
    }
}
```

